      "term": "mRNA vaccine",
      "definition": "A vaccine that uses a piece of genetic material (messenger RNA) to teach cells how to make a protein that triggers an immune response."
    },
    {
      "term": "Interferon",
      "definition": "A protein produced by the body's cells as a defensive response to viruses or other stimuli, which helps coordinate the immune response."
